<item>
            <title>[BATCH-999] JobExecution ExecutionContext should not be persisted by Step?</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-999</link>
                <project id="10090" key="BATCH">Spring Batch</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JobExecution ExecutionContext should not be persisted by Step?  I can see a hopeful looking comment added in 1.1 inside SimpleJobRepository:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public void updateExecutionContext(StepExecution stepExecution) &lt;/p&gt;
{
		// Until there is an interface change (
		ecDao.persistExecutionContext(stepExecution.getJobExecution());
		ecDao.persistExecutionContext(stepExecution);
	}

&lt;p&gt;We should re-visit that before 2.0 gets to a release candidate.  Caused problems for someone on the forum as well (&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=66030&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=66030&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
